title: Canada PM Trudeau, Trump discuss border cooperation, lumber
text:
20pm EST Canada PM Trudeau, Trump discuss border cooperation, lumber DAY 25 / FEBRUARY 13: President Donald Trump said the United States would be ''tweaking'' its trade relationship with Canada, stopping short of calling for a major realignment in a development likely to please visiting Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau. REUTERS/Carlos Barria 
OTTAWA Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau spoke with U.S. President Donald Trump on Thursday and the two leaders discussed cooperation along the countries' shared border as well as a dispute over lumber exports, Trudeau's office said. 
Dozens of asylum seekers, worried about Trump's plans for cracking down on immigration, have been crossing into Canada in recent weeks, putting a strain on border communities. 
(Reporting by David Ljunggren, editing by G Crosse) Next In World News
